# Project structure

**An Average RPG** — pnpm monorepo (`pnpm-workspace.yaml`). Firebase project: `an-average-rpg`.

## Top-level layout

```
├── apps/web/          # React + Vite frontend (the live game UI)
├── functions/         # Firebase Cloud Functions (authoritative game logic)
├── packages/shared/   # Shared TypeScript types, Zod schemas, constants
├── game-data/         # Static JSON content (classes, skills, dungeons, etc.)
├── crates/            # Rust game simulation (game-core) + WASM bindings (game-wasm)
├── .github/workflows/ # CI: web-pages.yml (web build + Firebase + GitHub Pages)
├── firebase.json      # Firestore, Storage, Functions, emulator config
├── firestore.rules    # Security rules
└── storage.rules
```

**Workspace packages:** `apps/*`, `packages/*`, `functions`. Root scripts delegate via `pnpm --filter`.

## Architecture

```
GitHub Pages (static)     Firebase
  apps/web/dist    →    Auth, Firestore, Cloud Functions, Storage
```

- **Client is untrusted.** Combat, rewards, death, inheritance, bank ops, and skill claims run in **Cloud Functions** (`functions/src/actions/`).
- **Firestore** holds live player state (`lineages`, heirs, bank, missions, etc.).
- **game-data/** is read-only content imported by the web app (`@game-data` alias) — not written at runtime.

## `apps/web/src/` conventions

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `features/` | Route-level pages (`CharacterPage`, `TavernPage`, …) — one folder per game area |
| `components/` | Reusable UI (`layout/`, `game/`, `skills/`) |
| `firebase/` | Firebase init (`config.ts`), callable wrappers (`functions.ts`), Firestore helpers, `*Bootstrap.ts` seed/setup |
| `stores/` | Zustand state (`authStore`, `gameStore`, `uiStore`) |
| `hooks/` | Custom React hooks |
| `lib/` | Pure helpers (missions, skills, tavern, validation) — often reads `@game-data` |
| `constants/` | App-wide constants — **`version.ts`** holds `APP_VERSION` |
| `types/` | Ambient types (e.g. `game-data.d.ts` for JSON imports) |

**Path alias:** `@/` → `apps/web/src/`. **Game data alias:** `@game-data` → repo root `game-data/`.

**Routing:** `App.tsx` → `/login` public; everything else inside `GameShell` + `ProtectedRoute`. Default route: `/character`.

**Live state flow:** `GameShell` subscribes to Firestore (`lineages`, active heir) → `gameStore`. Pages call `firebase/functions.ts` callables for mutations.

## `functions/`

- `src/index.ts` — exports all callable functions.
- `src/actions/` — one file per game action (`createHeir`, `resolveDungeon`, `claimSkill`, …).
- `src/utils/` — shared server helpers and types.
- Builds to `functions/lib/` (gitignored). Deployed via `web-pages.yml` (`deploy-firebase` job) using Workload Identity Federation or `FIREBASE_TOKEN`.

## `packages/shared/` (`@bloodline/shared`)

Single source of truth for **types** and **Zod schemas** used by web and functions. Import via `@bloodline/shared`, `@bloodline/shared/types`, etc. Add new domain types here before wiring UI or server code.

## `game-data/`

JSON content files: `classes.json`, `skills.json`, `dungeons.json`, `jobs.json`, `events.json`, `items.json`, `missions.json`, `races.json`, `subclasses.json`, `effects.json`, …

Changes here are **user-facing** — bump `APP_VERSION` when shipping.

## `crates/` (Rust / WASM)

- `game-core/` — simulation modules (combat, dungeons, skills, inheritance, …).
- `game-wasm/` — WASM bindings for the browser.

Build WASM: `pnpm build:wasm` → output under `apps/web/src/wasm`. Most gameplay authority still lives in Cloud Functions today.

## Where to put new work

| Change | Location |
|--------|----------|
| New screen / route | `apps/web/src/features/<area>/` + route in `App.tsx` + sidebar link |
| New server-side game rule | `functions/src/actions/` + export in `index.ts` + callable in `firebase/functions.ts` |
| New shared type/schema | `packages/shared/src/` |
| New class, skill, dungeon, event | `game-data/*.json` + types in `packages/shared` if needed |
| New Firestore collection/field | Function action + `firestore.rules` + client read in `GameShell` or feature page |

## Deploy & env

- **Local dev:** `pnpm dev` (web), `firebase emulators:start`, `apps/web/.env.local` (see `.env.example`).
- **Production web + Firebase:** push to `main` → `web-pages.yml` (build, `deploy-firebase`, then Pages).
